HIV/AIDS: Sin ta ce an samu karuwar sabon kamuwa da cutar da kashi 14 cikin 100
Kasar Sin ta ce ta samu karuwar mutane 14 cikin 100 da ke kamuwa da cutar HIV da AIDS.
Masu kula da lafiya sun ce mutane fiye da 820,000 ne ke fama da wannan cuta a ƙasar.
A cikin kwata na biyu na shekara ta 2018 ne aka samu kusan mutane 40,000 da suka kamu da cutar.
Yawancin sababbin cututtuka sun kasance na jima'i, wanda ya nuna cewa yanayin da ya gabata ya canja.
A wasu yankunan ƙasar Sin, an yi amfani da jini don yaɗa cutar.
Amma, an rage yawan mutanen da ke kamuwa da cutar ta HIV ta wannan hanyar zuwa kusan sifili, kamar yadda jami'an kiwon lafiya na kasar Sin suka ce a wani taro a lardin Yunnan.
A kowace shekara, adadin mutanen da ke kamuwa da cutar HIV da AIDS a kasar Sin yana ƙaruwa da mutane 100,000.
Yada HIV ta hanyar jima'i babbar matsala ce a cikin al'ummar LGBT a kasar Sin.
An kawar da cin zarafin luwaɗi a kasar Sin a shekara ta 1997, amma har yanzu ana nuna bambanci ga 'yan luwadi.
Bincike ya nuna cewa saboda ra'ayin da kasar ta nuna game da jima'i, kashi 70 zuwa 90 cikin 100 na maza da suke yin jima'i da maza suna aure mata.
A yawancin lokatai, ana iya samun cututtuka ta wurin rashin kāre waɗannan 'yancin yin jima'i.
Tun shekara ta 2003, gwamnatin Sin ta yi alkawarin samun maganin cutar HIV a ko'ina a duniya a matsayin wani ɓangare na ƙoƙarin magance wannan matsalar.
